hopobject.body: Do you know what extension he's on? pharmaconnect jobs The Telegraph made Talk Talk its mid-cap share tip of the week. Old Mutual fund manager Stephen Message told the paper he liked Talk Talk because customers stay with it despite its reputation for poor service. The shares yield a dividend of about 5% and there is room for growth from improving cash flows from better customer service and tight cost control, Message said. The company has enjoyed strong growth at its broadband-based telephone service.
